Instructions for running the project on a cloud-based platform:
Heroku

Create a new Heroku project.
Deploy the project code to Heroku.
Configure the OPENWEATHERMAP_API_KEY environment variable on Heroku.
Start the Heroku app.
AWS Lambda

Create a new AWS Lambda function.
Upload the project code to AWS Lambda.
Configure the OPENWEATHERMAP_API_KEY environment variable on AWS Lambda.
Deploy the AWS Lambda function.
Once the project is deployed on a cloud-based platform, you can start it by running the following command:

heroku local start
Or, if you are using AWS Lambda:

aws lambda invoke --function-name temperature-alert-agent --payload '{}' out.txt
